<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="196" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1358,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1502,1528]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Kobayashi, H. &amp; Nonaka, M." box="[329,671,1502,1529]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref9484" refString="Kobayashi, H. &amp; Nonaka, M. (2016) Molecular Phylogeny of the Notodontidae: Subfamilies Inferred from 28 S rRNA Sequences (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea, Notodontidae). Tinea, 23 (1), 1 - 83." type="journal article" year="2016">Kobayashi and Nonaka (2016)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kiriakoff, 1962)" baseAuthorityName="Kiriakoff" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[760,1133,1502,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinica">
<emphasis box="[760,934,1502,1528]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">Odnarda sinica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kiriakoff, S. G." box="[948,1124,1502,1529]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" pagination="149 - 214" refId="ref9406" refString="Kiriakoff, S. G. (1962) Notes sur les Notodontidae (Lepidoptera) Pydna Walker et Genres Voisins. Bulletin et Annales Societe d'Entomologi de Belgique, Series 2, 98, 149 - 214." type="journal article" year="1962">Kiriakoff, 1962</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
as the representative taxon to revive 
<taxonomicName authority="Kiriakoff, 1962" authorityName="Kiriakoff" authorityYear="1962" box="[260,544,1538,1564]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[260,360,1538,1564]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">Odnarda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kiriakoff, S. G." box="[369,544,1538,1564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" pagination="149 - 214" refId="ref9406" refString="Kiriakoff, S. G. (1962) Notes sur les Notodontidae (Lepidoptera) Pydna Walker et Genres Voisins. Bulletin et Annales Societe d'Entomologi de Belgique, Series 2, 98, 149 - 214." type="journal article" year="1962">Kiriakoff, 1962</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a full genus from the subgeneric status under the then extended concept of genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1857" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1857" box="[224,441,1574,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Biula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[224,285,1574,1600]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">Biula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[292,441,1574,1601]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" pagination="765 - 982" refId="ref10492" refString="Walker, F. (1857) [1858] List of the specimens of Lepidopterous Insects in the Collection of the British Museum, Part XII. Edward Newman, London, 217 pp. [pp. 765 - 982]" type="book chapter" year="1857">Walker, 1857</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of male genitalia and wing pattern. The basic structure of the 8 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1298,1311,1574,1588]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">th</superScript>
abdominal segment in the male genitalia is one of the simplest, yet best morphological synapomorphy for the species belonging to a genus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[305,461,1646,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodontidae</taxonomicName>
. The basic pattern of not only the 8 
<superScript attach="left" box="[864,877,1646,1660]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">th</superScript>
abdominal segment, but the entire male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schintlmeister, 1997)" baseAuthorityName="Schintlmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[181,696,1682,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Biula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leechi" subGenus="Odnarda">
<emphasis box="[181,441,1682,1708]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">Biula (Odnarda) leechi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schintlmeister, A." box="[454,687,1682,1709]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" pagination="33 - 248" refId="ref10114" refString="Schintlmeister, A. (1997) Moths of Vietnam with Special Reference to Mt. Fan-si-pan. Family Notodontidae. Entomofauna, 9 (4), 33 - 248." type="journal article" year="1997">Schintlmeister, 1997</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kiriakoff" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[919,1019,1683,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinica">
<emphasis box="[919,1019,1683,1709]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">O. sinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which undoubtedly groups these two species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kiriakoff" authorityYear="1962" box="[377,477,1718,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[377,477,1718,1744]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">Odnarda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schintlmeister, 1997)" authorityName="Mazumder &amp; Sanyal &amp; Schintlmeister &amp; Gayen &amp; Chandra &amp; Raha" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Schintlmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[613,1040,1718,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leechi">
<emphasis box="[613,786,1718,1744]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">Odnarda leechi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schintlmeister, A." box="[799,1032,1718,1745]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" pagination="33 - 248" refId="ref10114" refString="Schintlmeister, A. (1997) Moths of Vietnam with Special Reference to Mt. Fan-si-pan. Family Notodontidae. Entomofauna, 9 (4), 33 - 248." type="journal article" year="1997">Schintlmeister, 1997</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is being used as a new combination in this study.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1358,2033]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,573]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="196" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">
Forewing length: 
<specimenCount box="[397,418,1791,1817]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" type="male">â™‚</specimenCount>
<quantity box="[425,590,1790,1817]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.05" metricValueMin="1.95" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" unit="mm" value="20.0" valueMax="20.5" valueMin="19.5">19.5â€“20.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mazumder &amp; Sanyal &amp; Schintlmeister &amp; Gayen &amp; Chandra &amp; Raha" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Schintlmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[600,774,1790,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leechi">
<emphasis box="[600,774,1790,1816]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">Odnarda leechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belonging to the cryptic 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kiriakoff" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1052,1119,1791,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinica">
<emphasis box="[1052,1119,1791,1816]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">sinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-complex, resembles closely to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kiriakoff, 1962)" baseAuthorityName="Kiriakoff" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[181,486,1826,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinica">
<emphasis box="[181,283,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">O. sinica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kiriakoff, S. G." box="[298,478,1826,1853]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" pagination="149 - 214" refId="ref9406" refString="Kiriakoff, S. G. (1962) Notes sur les Notodontidae (Lepidoptera) Pydna Walker et Genres Voisins. Bulletin et Annales Societe d'Entomologi de Belgique, Series 2, 98, 149 - 214." type="journal article" year="1962">Kiriakoff, 1962</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Leech, 1898)" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[498,786,1826,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frugalis">
<emphasis box="[498,620,1826,1853]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">O. frugalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Leech, J. H." box="[636,777,1826,1853]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" pagination="261 - 379" refId="ref9528" refString="Leech, J. H. (1898) On Lepidoptera Heterocera from Northern China, Japan, Corea. The Transactions of the Entomological Society London, 1898, 261 - 379. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 22195" type="journal article" year="1898">Leech, 1898</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bryk, 1949)" baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[842,1160,1826,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboflavida">
<emphasis box="[842,1005,1826,1853]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">O. alboflavida</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bryk, F." box="[1020,1152,1826,1853]" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" pagination="1 - 51" refId="ref8949" refString="Bryk, F. (1949) Entomological Results from the Swedish Expedition 1934 to Burma and British India. Lepidoptera, Notodontidae Stephens, Cossidae Newman und Hepialidae Stephens. Arkiv for Zoologi, 42 A, 1 - 51." type="journal article" year="1949">Bryk, 1949</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Among these, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mazumder &amp; Sanyal &amp; Schintlmeister &amp; Gayen &amp; Chandra &amp; Raha" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Schintlmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1334,1436,1826,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leechi">
<emphasis box="[1334,1436,1826,1853]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">O. leechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is practically indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kiriakoff" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[571,674,1863,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinica">
<emphasis box="[571,674,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">O. sinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
externally except its paler colouration. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1131,1327,1862,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frugalis">
<emphasis box="[1131,1327,1862,1888]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">Odnarda frugalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has even darker colouration than both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mazumder &amp; Sanyal &amp; Schintlmeister &amp; Gayen &amp; Chandra &amp; Raha" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Schintlmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[485,589,1898,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leechi">
<emphasis box="[485,589,1898,1925]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">O. leechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kiriakoff" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[648,751,1899,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinica">
<emphasis box="[648,751,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">O. sinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Distinct blackish markings near the forewing apex present in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[182,306,1934,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frugalis">
<emphasis box="[182,306,1934,1961]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">O. frugalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is obsolete in the other three species mentioned here. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mazumder &amp; Sanyal &amp; Schintlmeister &amp; Gayen &amp; Chandra &amp; Raha" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Schintlmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[934,1110,1934,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leechi">
<emphasis box="[934,1110,1934,1960]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">Odnarda leechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the median prominent shadow and postmedian double rows of blackish specks as present in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[919,1080,1970,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboflavida">
<emphasis box="[919,1080,1970,1997]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">O. alboflavida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the male genitalia, the threearmed soccii is the best character to distinguish 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mazumder &amp; Sanyal &amp; Schintlmeister &amp; Gayen &amp; Chandra &amp; Raha" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Schintlmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[682,782,2006,2033]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leechi">
<emphasis box="[682,782,2006,2033]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="195">O. leechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the other three species which have two-armed soccii. Moreover, the elongated, deeply bilobed uncus, crescent shaped sclerotization in valve sacculus and more apically curved phallus are also typical to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mazumder &amp; Sanyal &amp; Schintlmeister &amp; Gayen &amp; Chandra &amp; Raha" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Schintlmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[527,629,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leechi">
<emphasis box="[527,629,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">O. leechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="196" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">Remarks:</emphasis>
Minor differences in the male genitalia of our specimens are observed when compared with that of 
<collectingCountry box="[182,277,259,285]" name="Vietnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
specimens as illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Schintlmeister, A." box="[589,836,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" pagination="33 - 248" refId="ref10114" refString="Schintlmeister, A. (1997) Moths of Vietnam with Special Reference to Mt. Fan-si-pan. Family Notodontidae. Entomofauna, 9 (4), 33 - 248." type="journal article" year="1997">Schintlmeister (1997)</bibRefCitation>
. The tegumen in the Vietnamese specimen is slightly broader and the 8 
<superScript attach="left" box="[353,366,294,308]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">th</superScript>
tergite is more deeply bilobed than those in our specimens. This species was described from North 
<collectingCountry box="[222,317,331,357]" name="Vietnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
within altitudinal range of 
<quantity box="[618,772,330,357]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.925" metricValueMax="2.25" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" unit="m" value="1925.0" valueMax="2250.0" valueMin="1600.0">1600â€“2250 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schintlmeister, A." box="[785,1015,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" pagination="33 - 248" refId="ref10114" refString="Schintlmeister, A. (1997) Moths of Vietnam with Special Reference to Mt. Fan-si-pan. Family Notodontidae. Entomofauna, 9 (4), 33 - 248." type="journal article" year="1997">Schintlmeister 1997</bibRefCitation>
). It was later found in 
<collectingCountry box="[1261,1328,331,357]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1342,1432,331,357]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,244,367,393]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[255,313,367,393]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">Tibet</collectingRegion>
up to 
<quantity box="[385,471,367,393]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" unit="m" value="3000.0">3000 m</quantity>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Schintlmeister, A." box="[494,723,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" refId="ref10146" refString="Schintlmeister, A. (2008) Palaearctic Macrolepidoptera. Vol. 1. Notodontidae. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 482 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004260993" type="book" year="2008">Schintlmeister 2008</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[786,895,367,393]" name="Myanmar" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
(pers. obs.). The present record from 
<collectingRegion country="India" name="Arunachal Pradesh" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">Arunachal Pradesh</collectingRegion>
not only extends its distribution limit, but also the altitudinal range of the species (
<figureCitation box="[1178,1247,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1321,1345]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,615,1268]" captionTargetId="figure-207@5.[151,1436,615,1268]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Map showing distributions of Odnarda leechi and Torona lucida with their Type localities." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5876515" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5876515/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Within Eastern Himalayan landscape, the species was particularly active in Sub-alpine Birch-Fir Forest distributed from 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" unit="m" value="3400.0" valueMax="3800.0" valueMin="3000.0">3000 to 3800 m</quantity>
altitudinal range. Moreover, the species will be the fourth under the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kiriakoff" authorityYear="1962" box="[1067,1167,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1067,1167,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">Odnarda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, known until now by 
<taxonomicName authority="(Moore, 1879)" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basistriga">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">O. basistriga</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, F." box="[279,430,511,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" pagination="5 - 299" refId="ref9741" refString="Moore, F. (1879) Heterocera. In: Hewitson, W. C. &amp; Moore, F. (Eds.), Descriptions of New Indian Lepidopterous Insects from the Collection of the Late Mr. W. S. Atkinson, M. A., F. I. S. &amp; C. Asiatic Society of Bengal, Calcutta. Issues 1 - 3. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, pp. 5 - 299." type="book chapter" year="1879">Moore, 1879</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hampson, 1892)" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[450,838,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrofasciata">
<emphasis box="[450,633,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">O. nigrofasciata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson, G. F." box="[649,830,511,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" refId="ref9180" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1892) The Fauna of British India Including Ceylon and Burma, Moths. Vol. I. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, 527 pp." type="book" year="1892">Hampson, 1892</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nakamura, 1974)" baseAuthorityName="Nakamura" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[895,1266,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Odnarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamurensis">
<emphasis box="[895,1052,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">O. tamurensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nakamura, M." box="[1067,1257,511,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" pagination="115 - 129" refId="ref9826" refString="Nakamura, M. (1974) Notodontidae of Eastern Nepal Based on the Collection of the Lepidopterological Research Expedition to Nepal Himalaya by the Lepidopterological Society of Japan in 1963 (Lepidoptera). Lepidoptera Science, 25 (4), 115 - 129. https: // doi. org / 10.18984 / lepid. 25.4 _ 115" type="journal article" year="1974">Nakamura, 1974</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1336,1396,511,537]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">India</collectingCountry>
, all the species being exclusively Himalayan in distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
